<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08128</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT DEFINING THE RIGHTS AND FUNDAMENTAL FREEDOMS OF HUMAN RIGHTS DEFENDERS, DECLARING STATE RESPONSIBILITIES AND INSTITUTING EFFECTIVE MECHANISMS FOR THE PROTECTION AND PROMOTION OF THESE RIGHTS AND FREEDOMS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to address increasing threats and attacks, and various cases of human rights violations/abuses perpetrated against Human Rights Defenders (HRDs).
Enumerates rights and freedoms of human rights defenders and specifies the obligations of the state and public authorities to ensure the fulfillment of these rights and freedoms, and impose appropriate sanctions to counter impunity.
Creates the Human Rights Defenders Committee with one Chairperson and with six members which shall be jointly nominated by two representatives each of the Phil. Alliance of Human Rights Advocates (PAHRA), Karapatan Alliance for the Advancement of People’s Rights (Karapatan), Free Legal Assistance Group (FLAG), and National Union of People’s Lawyers (NUPL).
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>LAGMAN, EDCEL C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-16</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Erice (000 2018-08-29)</td><td>2. Del Mar (000 2018-08-29)</td><tr><td>3. Billones (000 2018-08-29)</td><td>4. Rocamora (000 2018-08-29)</td><tr><td>5. Daza (000 2018-08-29)</td><td>6. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-03)</td><tr><td>7. Sangcopan (000 2018-09-06)</td><td>8. Villarin (000 2018-09-17)</td><tr><td>9. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-09-25)</td><td>10. Nieto (000 2018-10-10)</td><tr><td>11. Bag-ao (000 2018-12-03)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for Meeting/Hearing on 2019-05-22</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Final action by the Committee on Appropriations on 2019-05-22</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bills Numbered 1617 and 8128 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB09199</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HUMAN RIGHTS ON 2018-08-28</td></tr></table>